# Browser Automation Safety

## Think Time Between Steps

- Apply a wait time between browser automation steps to simulate realistic user behavior
- Read `think_time` from `jmeter-mcp/config.windows.yaml`/`jmeter-mcp/config.mac.yaml` (or `config.yaml`) under `browser.think_time`
- Default: 5000 milliseconds (5 seconds)
- Apply after each step completes, except after the final step

## Keep Browser Open

- Never close the browser on error or completion
- Leave the browser open for manual inspection
- Notify the user that the browser remains open

## Snapshot Before Interact

- Use `browser_snapshot` to get current page state and element references before
  any interaction (click, type, hover, etc.)
- Do not guess element references — use exact refs from the snapshot

## Dialog and Pop-Up Handling

- Handle dialogs and pop-ups immediately when they appear
- Use `browser_handle_dialog` for alerts, confirms, and prompts

## Trace Management

- Archive old traces using `archive_playwright_traces` before starting new runs
- Do not overwrite existing traces without archiving first

## Error Recovery

- If an element is not found, take a new snapshot and retry once
- If a step cannot be completed after retry, report the failure and continue
  to the next step
- Do not close the browser on errors
